<topic id="dcpp_how_to_reset_the_page_numbers_at_each_chapter">
  <title>How to Number Pages within Chapter Scope</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            ><ph keyref="html5-transformation"/><indexterm>Numbering<indexterm>Reset page
                numbers<indexterm>at each chapter</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="pdf-css">Numbering<indexterm>Reset page numbers<indexterm>at each
              chapter</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To make the page numbers start from 1, reset the <codeph>page</codeph> counter at each of the
			topics marked as chapters:</p>
    <codeblock outputclass="language-css">*[class ~= "topic/topic"][is-chapter]{
  counter-reset:page 1 section1 tablecount figcount !important;
}  </codeblock>
  </body>
</topic>
